CommonFields.Title: Comparative studies for the effect of intercalating agent on the physical properties of epoxy resin-clay based nanocomposite materials
Author: Dai, Chung-Feng
Li, Pei-Ru
Yeh, Jui-Ming
CommonFields.Location: Department of Chemistry, Center for Nanotechnology at CYCU and R&D Center for Membrane Technology, Chung-Yuan Christian University, Chung Li 32023, Taiwan, ROC

Mixing.Description: 5 g of MMT clay with a CEC value of 115 mEq/100 g was stirred at rt overnight in beaker A.
The calculated amount of dodecyltriphenyl-phosphonium bromide was magnetically stirred in beaker B

ChooseParameter.Other: 1.0 M HCl aqueous solution is added to beaker B to adjust pH value to 3-4

Mixing.Description: The mixture in beaker B was stirred for 3 hours

ChooseParameter.Other: Beaker B was added at a rate of approximately 10 mL/min with vigorous stirring to the MMT suspension (beaker A)

Mixing.Description: The mixture was then stirred overnight at rt.

ChooseParameter.Other: After centrifugation, the clear solution was decanted.
Products were washed with 500 mL of distilled water for 0.5 - 1 hr for purification
The two previous steps (washing and centrifugation) were repeated 5 times to remove excess ammonium ions

Filler.Description: The organophilic clay was prepared by a cationic exchange method

Mixing.Description: 1 g of TGTPM was dissolved in 12 g of DMAc under stirring

ChooseParameter.Other: The as-prepared organophilic MMT clay was introduced.

Mixing.Description: 0.54 g of T-403 was added to the mixture and stirring continued for 12 hrs at rt.

ChooseParameter.Other: It was then drop-wisely cast onto a clean Teflon mould

MoldingInfo.Description: After drop-wisely casting, the sample was cured.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: Heating rate of 3 C/min and at a frequency of 1 Hz

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: The scan rate was 10 C/min, and temperature range was from 30 C to 900 C
